Based on this approach, Roquette has defined 4 internal criteria for measuring the sustainable development impact of its innovation projects:

                           -

Waste prevention (based on principle 1 of green chemistry);


                           -

Atom economy, high yield (based on principles 2 & 8);


                           -

Reduction of hazards (based on principles 3, 4, 5 & 12);


                           -

Energy efficiency and benign operating conditions (based on principles 6 & 12).
